    <summary>Ferrum-language compiler — systems programming with compile-time memory safety</summary>
    <description>## Ferrum-language Compiler

Ferrum-language is a systems programming language with C syntax and compile-time memory safety via a borrow checker and ownership model. Compiled to native code through LLVM 18.

### Features

- **Ownership and move semantics** — memory managed at compile time, no GC
- **Immutable and mutable borrows** enforced at compile time
- **Opt-in unsafe blocks** for raw pointer arithmetic and FFI
- **C interoperability** via `#include`
- **Zero runtime overhead** — no garbage collector, no reference counting
- **LLVM 18 backend** — full optimizations, fast native code

### Usage

```
ferrumc hello.fe -o hello
hello.exe
```

### Links

- Homepage: https://ferrum-language.github.io/Ferrum/
- Source: https://github.com/Ferrum-Language/Ferrum
- Issues: https://github.com/Ferrum-Language/Ferrum/issues
- Releases: https://github.com/Ferrum-Language/Ferrum/releases
    </description>
    <releaseNotes>## v0.3.0

Initial public release of the Ferrum-language compiler.

- Full borrow checker implementation
- Ownership and move semantics
- Mutable and immutable references
- Unsafe blocks for low-level programming
- C interoperability via #include
- LLVM 18 backend for native code generation
- Windows x86_64 support

Full changelog: https://github.com/Ferrum-Language/Ferrum/releases/tag/v0.3.0
    </releaseNotes>
